# Agent Rule Loading

Before implementing, reviewing, or editing docs/code in this repo, agents must read the applicable `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` files for the paths they will touch.

Minimum rule-loading requirements:

- For any `services/ai-backend/**` work, read:
  - `.cursor/rules/ai-backend-engineering.mdc`
  - `.cursor/rules/ai-backend-python.mdc` when touching Python code
  - `.cursor/rules/ai-backend-spec-first.mdc` when touching AI backend docs/specs
  - `.cursor/rules/ai-backend-testing.mdc` when touching tests
- For workspace architecture or service boundary work, read:
  - `.cursor/rules/workspace-architecture.mdc`
  - `.cursor/rules/service-boundaries.mdc`
- For `apps/frontend/**` work, read:
  - `.cursor/rules/frontend-app.mdc`
  - `.cursor/rules/frontend-design-system.mdc` when touching shared UI usage
- For `services/backend/**` or `services/backend-facade/**` work, read:
  - `.cursor/rules/backend-services.mdc`
- For `packages/api-types/**` work, read:
  - `.cursor/rules/packages-api-types.mdc`
- For `packages/design-system/**` work, read:
  - `.cursor/rules/frontend-design-system.mdc`
- For CI/CD, Docker, or workflow work, read:
  - `.cursor/rules/ci-cd-docker.mdc`

Do not assume rule contents from memory. Re-read the rule files in the current workspace before making changes.
